[As mentioned previously, this website is constantly updated as new information comes in, so it is likely that when you read this post, the numbers will not match the linked numbers because they will have been updated since the post was prepared.

According to the data on the Johns Hopkins website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 110 041, with 80 735 cases reported by mainland China. There are now a total of 29 279 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 107 countries/locations outside mainland China, representing an increase of 3947 cases reported in the past 24 hours, with Italy accounting for 1492 of the newly reported cases, Iran for 743 of newly reported cases, and South Korea for 248 of newly reported cases. There are 24 other countries experiencing increases of more than 10 cases: France, 260; Germany, 240; Spain, 148; USA, 119; Netherlands, 77; Switzerland, 69; UK, 64; Japan, 41; Sweden, 42; Egypt, 34; Belgium, 31; Greece, 27; Austria, 23; Norway, 20; Israel, 18; Australia, 13; San Marino, 13; Denmark, 12; Czech Republic, 12; Viet Nam, 12; Singapore, 12; Canada, 10; Lebanon, 10; and Portugal, 10. A global total of 3825 deaths have been reported, 706 outside mainland China.

For the 12th consecutive day, more cases have been reported from outside mainland China than within mainland China. - Mod.MPP]

