[According to the report above, a total of 80 735 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from China, representing an increase of 40 cases in the past 24 hours, of which 36 (90%) were in Hubei province. It is the 2nd consecutive day that the number of newly reported cases in a 24 hour period was less than 50. In addition, 22 deaths were reported, with 21 (95.5%) were reported by Hubei province. Five new cases were reported from Hong Kong.

Of note is the increasing numbers of imported cases mentioned with 4 newly imported cases (all in Gansu), bringing the total number of imported cases to 67. If the imported cases are counted in the daily totals, then 10% of the newly confirmed cases mentioned in today's (8 Mar 2020) update were imported cases. It would be of interest to know where the importations originated.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html, and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7066281,155. - Mod.MPP]

