[The tally of confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Italy is now 7375, including 366 deaths, up from 5061 cases and 233 deaths reported on 7 Mar 2020. Cases continue to be concentrated in Lombardy (4189), the epicenter of the outbreak, Emilia-Romagna (1180), and Venice (670), all in the northern part of the county. Italy is a major tourist point, Lombardy is a major commercial hub, and Italians themselves are highly mobile and travel throughout Europe and the Americas. See section [4] below for imported cases from Italy to other countries in Europe and in other regions, a sign of this mobility.

In the past 24 hours, Italy has announced plans to effect a lockdown of the northern provinces. See section [5] below for more details

A map of Italy showing regions can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/italy/regions.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7066281,75. - Mod.MPP]

