[In the past 24 hours, the number of cases of COVID-19 confirmed in Iran has grown from 5823 to 6566 an increase of 743 newly confirmed cases. The number of deaths has also increased from 145 to 194, an increase of 49 deaths in the past 24 hours.

Qom, while the apparent original epicenter of this outbreak, is located to the south west of Tehran in central Iran. Tehran is now the epicenter of the outbreak with 1805 (an increase of 266 cases from yesterday 7 Mar 2020) confirmed cases. Cases have now been confirmed in all of the 31 provinces in the country.

A map of Iran showing provinces can be seen at https://www.mapsofworld.com/iran/iran-political-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7066281,128 - Mod.MPP]

