ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Given the experiences we've seen with the Diamond Princess, the Grand Princess, the Nile River cruise ship, learning that crew from the Diamond Princess was shifted to work on other ships, and the observation that individuals (passengers) have boarded ships with mild symptoms, and then progressed on to have a full clinical picture with pneumonia, it does appear that for the time being, cruising may not be the healthiest vacation to take, especially for those older than 60 years of age, and/or with pre-existing co-morbidities, including hypertension, cardiovascular disease, renal disease, history of malignancies on chemotherapy, and the list goes on.

In another media report, it is mentioned that "the new CDC guidance also warns the elderly and those with underlying health problems to avoid non-essential travel such as long plane trips." (https://www.politico.com/news/2020/03/08/cdc-warns-plane-trips-cruises-coronavirus-124153). - Mod.MPP]

