[The number of countries and territories reporting confirmed cases of COVID-19 outside China continues to grow and now totals 102. This includes 9 countries from the Western Pacific region, 49 countries (including 2 territories) from the European region, 7 countries from the Southeast Asia region, 16 countries (including 1 territory) from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 15 countries (including 4 territories) from the Americas region, and 6 countries from the African region. 53 countries/territories are listed as having local transmission within their countries, with Cambodia, Austria, Hungary, Peru and Brazil newly reporting local transmission. Local transmission and clusters of cases was also noted on the cruise ship that was quarantined in Japan (the Diamond Princess) and the cruise ship on the Nile in Egypt.

The total number of cases reported from outside of China is now 24 727 including 484 deaths.

A somewhat repetitive but necessary reminder: it is clear that the number of reported confirmed cases differs from different reporting websites and is somewhat a function of time of day the website is updated. For example, I note the time I've accessed the Johns Hopkins website, but by the time the post is actually finished with the editing process, those numbers have at times significantly changed. Case counting is clearly a moving target, and, depending upon when the website updates, the numbers may be different. - Mod.MPP]
